# Discord Bot Configuration

## Required Environment Variables
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID=your_application_id_here

## Optional Configuration
POMODORO_DEFAULT_WORK_DURATION=25m
POMODORO_DEFAULT_SHORT_BREAK=5m
POMODORO_DEFAULT_LONG_BREAK=15m
POMODORO_DEFAULT_LONG_BREAK_INTERVAL=4

## Bot Permissions Required:
# - Send Messages (2048)
# - Use Slash Commands (2147483648)
# - Embed Links (16384)
# - Mention Everyone (131072) - optional, for role notifications
# - Read Message History (65536)
# Total permissions integer: 2147695616

## Bot Invite URL Template:
# https://discord.com/api/oauth2/authorize?client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID&permissions=2147695616&scope=bot%20applications.commands

## How to get your bot token:
# 1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
# 2. Create a new application
# 3. Go to "Bot" section and create a bot
# 4. Copy the bot token and paste it above
# 5. Go to "OAuth2" > "URL Generator"
# 6. Select scopes: "bot" and "applications.commands"
# 7. Select the bot permissions listed above
# 8. Use the generated URL to invite the bot to your server